										<paragraph>
											<content ID="a2">The symptoms described during this call suggest that the problem concerned can be managed at home</content>
										</paragraph>
										<paragraph>If symptoms persist we recommend that you discuss the symptoms with your GP</paragraph>
										<paragraph>Diarrhoea is common and usually resolves in less than one week</paragraph>
										<paragraph>There is no evidence that fasting will have any benefit</paragraph>
										<paragraph>Increased fluid intake and changes to the diet are the best treatment for diarrhoea to replace fluid losse</paragraph>
										<paragraph>Include fruit juices, soups and foods high in carbohydrate, such as bread, pasta, potatoes or rice</paragraph>
										<paragraph>Oral rehydration fluids from the pharmacist help to replace lost sugars and salt preventing dehydration</paragraph>
										<paragraph>WORSENING:If symptoms persist, worsen or any new symptoms develop, call us back</paragraph>
